<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 02 at 4:09PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Floyd,
western Gordon and northeastern Chattooga Counties through 445 PM
EDT...
At 409 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Armuchee, or 9 miles
east of Summerville, moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Calhoun, Resaca, Plainville, Oostanaula, Sugar Valley, Tidings,
Everett Springs and Lake Marvin.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
